course_title: Women's Health Nurse Practitioner III: Preceptorship for Women's Health
course_description: Students are given an opportunity to focus primarily on the refinement of advanced practice skills by functioning fully as a WHNP. Seminars, conducted by case management, will assist the student in analysis and synthesis of the role of the WHNP in today's health care environment.
prerequisites: NRSG 601 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
